Economic growth figures out today could reveal that the country's economy is in another recession. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Economic growth figures could reveal that the country's economy is in another recession. That's defined by two consecutive quarters of negative growth. READ: Coronavirus spreads in three continents; markets brace for uncertainty The economy shrunk by 0.6 percent between July and September last year. Some economists believe the October-to-December number to be released by Stats SA on Tuesday, will be in the negative as well.